comment_data.body: Here we need to check and manage returned value.

```suggestion
        if (PyObject_HasAttr(v, PYIDENT("__set_name__"))) {
            PyObject_CallMethodObjArgs(v, PYIDENT("__set_name__"),  (PyObject *) tp, k, NULL);
```

Fairly minor, but I think this should be slightly faster - partly because it only creates the `"__set_name__"` string once at module startup and partly because the function call should be quicker.

(`PYIDENT` is a Cython trick when processing utility code to substitute out reused strings).

With that said, this isn't really performance sensitive so doesn't matter too much.
Thank you @da-woods. I am not expert in C API so any advice is highly appreciated.

It's enough to declare this locally where it's needed. That avoids reasoning about dangling pointers when reading the code.
```suggestion
```

commit.message:
Call __set_name__ during setting type attribute.

Based on https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__set_name__
